    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>LOWER PRICE FOR AUCTIONEER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Suzanne Kapner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Kapner, Suzanne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>British Internet auctioneer QXL agrees to acquire German rival Ricardo.de (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The British Internet auctioneer QXL agreed to buy a German rival, Ricardo.de, although it lowered its original offer by nearly three-quarters, to 171 million [pounds], or $256.5 million, after learning that Ricardo's fourth-quarter revenue had declined sharply. The deal values Ricardo at 32.9 euros, or about $29.94, a share, compared with QXL's original bid, made in May, of 42.6 euros a share. Ricardo will provide QXL with an entry into the German market, where a United States competitor, eBay, is the leader.</p>
        <p>Suzanne Kapner (NYT)</p>
      </block>
